    "body": "Here is the code snippet taken from the documentation [here](https://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/tutorial/pure.html#static-typing), I've no idea if the documentation is wrong or if it is the Cython compiler that has a bug.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\n@cython.cclass\r\nclass A:\r\n    cython.declare(a=cython.int, b=cython.int)\r\n    c = cython.declare(cython.int, visibility='public')\r\n    d = cython.declare(cython.int, 5)  # private by default.\r\n    e = cython.declare(cython.int, 5, visibility='readonly')\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe output of the test suite:\r\n\r\n```\r\nRunning tests against Cython 0.29a0 ff577a2baf4aebacd1a2f9bebd769e05e5d05ae1\r\n\r\n...\r\n\r\n=== C/C++ compiler error output: ===\r\ntotest.c: In function 'PyInit_totest':\r\ntotest.c:2729:3: error: 'd' undeclared (first use in this function)\r\n   d = 5;\r\n   ^\r\ntotest.c:2729:3: note: each undeclared identifier is reported only once for each function it appears in\r\ntotest.c:2736:3: error: 'e' undeclared (first use in this function)\r\n   e = 5;\r\n   ^\r\n==============================\r\nERROR\r\n```",
